22/04/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The country's main opposition Social Democratic Party (SDP) will hold an extraordinary congress on June 2nd to elect a new party leader. The SDP main board decided the date on Saturday (April 21st). The chairmanship was left vacant earlier this month after SPD president Ivica Racan, who is suffering from cancer, announced his withdrawal from politics. (Vecernji List - 22/04/07; HINA, HRT -21/04/07)
